content.webTitle: Viduka ready to eliminate the country of his parents

fields.headline: Viduka ready to eliminate the country of his parents
fields.bodyText: Mark Viduka has said he will not have a problem playing for Australia against Croatia despite his parents being Croatian. "I suppose it is a natural thing to ask why I am not playing for Croatia but why would I? I am Australian through and through," he said. "The game will be special for me. But it will be special because a draw will get us through to the next round and not because of my background and the fact that it is against Croatia."
